First things first - Vampire Fleets is great!!!

I was waiting to see when and how the friendly virus would be introduced
into the universe, and VF did it well.

Few questions though:

1) On page 15, the referee\'s notes on Aight say it has an operational
starport, whilst the subsector map and UPP on page 14 says class X, which
I take as no starport. The same applies to Matunuck on the map, but it has
an E class starport on the UPP.
Ihishi, 3204 on the map on p14 has no starport, on the UPP on the same page
is is given as having a D class starport.
On page 19 the referee\'s notes on Exeter says the world has no operational
starport, and then says in the next paragraph that Romrugo of Vars, the 
most powerful of the TEDs controls the starport and a fleet of 3 armed 
spacecraft. Does Exeter have a starport?

2) The Star City surface map had a symbol in the Map Key for Compute HQ (
....er ignore the last line, just figured out that Compute HQ (and tube
station) referred to the members of the sentient council, and not one of
them.
What is the Large Hex superimposed over several hexes in the Downport region?

3) Are we going to get a Covenant of Suffren sourcebook? I was dissapointed
that Vampire Fleets didn\'t have more info on it. The article on the Covenant
in Challenge 76 blew me away!

Thats all, roll on Keepers of the Flame!

Eamon Watters, CNG0016@qub.v2.ac.uk
