    'body' => '
Hi,

I was reconsidering fusion rockets (and trying to characterize the exact 
differences between them and HEPlaR (since we know HEPlaR is just a fusion
rocket given the energy of the exhaust vs. energy in)...

Drive type      TL		Thrust		FC    		%disp./gturn
----      --		----		---- 		----

Fusion Rkt      9		9		.00035		.1775

HEPlaR          10		200		.00088		.4464


The fusion rocket is 2.5143 times more efficient in fuel use, but the drives
are huge (around 8% of disp. per g).  I was thinking of adding an "extra
dirty"
HEPlaR that would look like this:

Drive type      TL		Thrust		FC        	 %disp./gturn
----      --		----		----    	 ----

Dirty HEPlaR    12 		 200		.00035		.1775


It just gives a traditional HEPlaR the FC of the fusion rocket.  I picked
TL12
since that\'s when damper technology (and hence strong/weak manipulation)
comes
into play.  The point was to get a few more gturns for ships that don\'t have
to
land on populated planets.

On a practical level (converting designs) it allows you to simply multiply
the
number of gturns of fuel by 2.51----which would give military ships that are
tight designs with just 50gturns, 125 gturns to play with.

I like this \'cause we wanted ships to be a little closer to CT, and I can
still
design FFS ships, and have a note at the bottom that says "if you want a more
CT feel, treat the exhaust as you would a fusion rocket, and multiply all
gturns
of fuel by 2.51 (unless you are running the drive "clean"----more inert 
propellant, less direct fusion)".

What do you think?

-Merrick

