Fuel used = (DV*J*5)/MJ

where   DV = jump drive volume
        J  = jump distance in parsecs
        MJ = maximum jump possible (with this drive)

e.g. A TL 15 jump drive with a volume of 100m^3 would require
(100*2*5)/5 or 200m^3 for a jump of 2 parsecs.
